5 to switch - a trigger are used to switch a state.
6 to support - Microsoft doesn't support Windows XP.
7 to retool  - a system administrator has to retool its workplace.
8 to implement - a class implements a interface.
9 to run a program - You should run Firefox to browse the Internet
10 to enable - Acronis enables to backup a data.
11 to utilize - Programmers utilizes a various api of services.
12 language features - trait is  language features of PHP.
13 multithreaded - Java is a multithreaded programming language.
14 electronic appliance - electronic appliances is used everywhere.
15 embedded systems  - embedded systems based on a Raspberry Pi.
16 to complete a course  - I will try to complete a course.
17 to require - that library requires other dependencies.
18 optional - that functional is optional.
19 assignment - I got the first assignment.
20 to expand  - That post expand your powers.
21 to assist - a support should assist with a matter
22 to allow  - multithreaded allows to speed up data processing.
23 to contain - A virtual mashine can contain other virtual mashines.
24 placeholder - To continue you should fill placeholders
25 lowercase letter - :
26 capital letter - the editor allows you to enter lowercase letter and capital letter
27 purpose -   the purpose of an Information Technology is to help people carry out their work easier.
